A YOUNG TEEN [D-SHOT] WHO SEEMS HEADED FOR COLLEGE, ALL OF A SUDDEN NEEDS MONEY TO KEEP HIM AND HIS FAMILY FROM GETTING THROWN OUT OF THEIR HOUSE. UNFORTUNATELY, HE GETS THE MONEY FROM AN OLD ENEMY [E-40] WHO HAPPENS TO BE A DRUG DEALER. SOON, HE BEGINS TO GET SUCKED IN TO THE HUSTLING LIFESTYLE. WELL, THIS IS QUITE OK FOR A MOVIE THAT RELIES ON A LOTTA RAPPERS FOR A CAST. THIS AIN'T TOO BAD, IT IS WATCHABLE. ONLY PROBLEM I HAVE WITH THIS FILM IS THAT IT RIPPED OFF THE OPENING CREDITS OF ''BOYZ N THE HOOD''. BUT OTHER THAN THAT, IT'S A SUPRISINGLY WATCHABLE FILM.
